$ libc: scanf family

The scanf family is the complement to the → development/languages/C-C-plus-plus/C/libc/functions/printf[`printf` family].
It decomposes a string into parts and assigns the values of these parts to variables.

{ Macros for format strings #scanf-macros

  `SCN{fmt}{type}`. Compare with the → development/languages/C-C-plus-plus/C/libc/functions/printf#printf-macros[`printf` macros].

}

sa:
  → development/languages/C-C-plus-plus/C/libc
